According to various polls and commentators, President Donald Trump's State of the Union Address was well-received by the American people. A POLITICO/Morning Consult poll found that 62% of viewers rated Trump's performance as "excellent" or "good." An NBC News/Survey Monkey poll revealed that 60% of viewers felt that Trump focused on the right things, and a CBS News poll showed that 75% of Americans approved of the speech. Commentators praised Trump's speech for its inclusiveness, vision, and ability to unite the country. Overall, the address was seen as a strong and positive performance by the President.